I made a script that builds the sprite using `dist/icons.json`, so it must be run after the current main build. The SVG attributes of the inner linked file in the `<use />` tag don't work, so the SVG attributes, class or style must be passed when using the inline SVG tag. Just like this:
```html
<svg [feather svg attributes, css class atrtibute, style attribute]>
  <use xlink:href="[spriteFileUrl]#[iconID]"/>
</svg>
```
The following CSS class was extracted from the default icon attributes and renders it nicely:
```css
.feather {
  width: 24px; 
  height: 24px; 
  stroke: currentColor; 
  stroke-width: 2; 
  stroke-linecap: round; 
  stroke-linejoin: round; 
  fill: none
}
```
